A lot of us - myself included - use UTC time at times, when we're dealing with people and actions on a global scale. 1200Z is 1200Z across the globe. But that day/night thing makes us need to shift to the 24 time zones because if you want to do business during the day with someone across the globe, you prefer to do it during their daylight hours. </p><p>

