		 	<span id="comment_score_64304003" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64304003); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>2</a>)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~Ol+Olsoc">Ol Olsoc</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~Ol+Olsoc">( 1175323 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64304003"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64304003">If you live nearer the equator, Daylight saving s time is useless, It's stupid, and only stupid people like it. <p>

If you live in the northern/southern temperate zones, where there are rather large swings in day/night length, it makes very good sense, as getting light at 4 in the morning, or dark at 4:30 in the afternoon is perhaps not optimum. So you adjust the time of day to make the living and working conditions align more with people liking to work in light, and relax and sleep in darkness</p><p>

Further North<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64304003">

